data.title: Oliver Cahill
data.meta_description: "A big part of why I joined this profession is that it brings me joy to be able to help clients achieve their ongoing financial goals, as well as building strong relationships with each client."
data.text:
Oliver commenced with WARR HUNT in March 2023.

Oliver has a Bachelor of Business (Economics and Finance) and is currently completing a Graduate Diploma in Financial Planning. Working closely with our senior advisors, he is looking forward to commencing his professional year and taking on a lead advisor role in short term.

Prior to joining the firm, Oliver gained sound experience in Client Services and Associate roles in financial services.

Oliver is originally from country Victoria, playing football at club level. He is a North Melbourne supporter. Now he enjoys training and competing in Triathlons.

Qualifications & Accreditations

Bachelor of Business (Economics and Finance), RMIT

Professional Memberships

Financial Advice Association Australia (FAAA), Graduate Member
